# Backend architecture (scoped)

When editing server/API code:

1. Load skill `backend-architecture` for new endpoints, services, or schema work
2. Handlers stay thin — business logic in service layer
3. Parameterized queries only; validate all inputs at boundary
4. Consistent error envelope and HTTP semantics
5. AuthZ in services, not only at route edge
6. Timeouts on all external calls

Surface trade-offs for persistence, caching, and async before implementing.
